    "comment": "<div><span style=\"font-family:Roboto; font-size:12pt; font-variant:normal; letter-spacing:0pt; vertical-align:baseline; font-weight:400; color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\">1 - If a customer selects ‘Purchase Order’ as the Payment Method during Checkout, the PO field is a mandatory field.&nbsp;&nbsp;We have found that the PO# is not always displayed on the order documents.</span><br /></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Roboto; font-size:12pt; font-variant:normal; letter-spacing:0pt; vertical-align:baseline; font-weight:400; color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\">Please see attached.&nbsp;&nbsp;Alliance Elevator paid via a Purchase Order but the PO Line details are missing from the order documents.&nbsp;&nbsp;Vantage Elevator attachment is an example of how it should be displayed. </span><br /></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Roboto; font-size:12pt; font-variant:normal; letter-spacing:0pt; vertical-align:baseline; font-weight:400; color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\">We are concerned about why this appears to happen on a random basis. </span><br /></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Roboto; font-size:12pt; font-variant:normal; letter-spacing:0pt; vertical-align:baseline; font-weight:400; font-style:italic; color:rgb(255, 0, 0)\">Files sent to channel</span><br /></div>",
